<h1>A Palette of Multiresolution Applications</h1>
<font color=green>
A privileged insight into data and information.
Applications in medicine, astronomy, surveillance and security, Earth 
observation, telecommunications, financial engineering, multimedia, 
plasma physics, and many other areas.

<p>

<font color=blue>
<hr><p>
<li> <b><a href="comet.html">Comet nucleus</a></b> - looking into the nucleus 
and surroundings of a comet.
<li> <b><a href="heart.html">Echocardiography</a></b> - using ulstrasound to 
non-invasively see the structure of the heart. 
<li> <b><a href="mines.html">Surveillance</a></b> - where is the minefield?
<li> <b><a href="ngc2997.html">Galaxy and stars</a></b> - 
separating into layers what we observe.
<li> <b><a href="noise.html">Noise</a></b> - an ever-present foe.
<li> <b><a href="mammo.html">Mammogram</a></b> - for image transfer to
breast cancer specialists.
<li> <b><a href="sar.html">Radar view of Earth</a></b> - as seen from the 
European Space Agency's ERS synthetic aperture radar satellites.
<li> <b><a href="edge.html">Architectural backbone</a></b> - the linear 
components of a street scene.
<li> <b><a href="envir.html">Jetstream</a></b> - 
showing the superimposed fluctuations 
that make up most environmental phenomena.
<li> <b><a href="fin.html">Predicting the S&P 500 index</a></b> - financial 
engineering, using the elasticity of time.
<li> <b><a href="telec.html">Web middleware engineering</a></b> - observation,
interpretation and forecasting of telecommunications traffic.
<li> <b><a href="hyper.html">Text and hypertext</a></b> - information 
discovery and retrieval.
</ul>
